  "text": "One male amygdala-lesioned animal died at approximately 1 year of age due to unrelated causes [CITATION_1] and was subsequently replaced with an alternative age-matched amygdala-lesioned male. The substitute subject was reared with his mother only for the first year of life. At 1 year of age, the animal was weaned and pair housed with an age-matched female until being introduced to his current cohort at approximately 1 year and 3 months of age.",
